{"lemma":"تَرْتِيل","slug":"تَرْتِيل","root":"ر.ت.ل","root_slug":"ر-ت-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ت-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"تَرْتِيل","root":"رتل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14711"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%84"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"hymnody"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"slow and measured recitation","examples":[{"text":"وَرَتِّلِ الْقُرْآنَ تَرْتِيلًا","english":"and recite the Qur'an in slow measured rhythmic tones"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the verbal noun of رَتَّلَ (rattala)"},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14711","headword_ar":"تَرْتِيلٌ","root":"rtl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", in its original sense, relates to the teeth; signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tafoliyj","text_ar":"تَفْلِيج"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof [i. e., as inf. n. of the verb in its pass. form, Their"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being separate, one from another"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Bd in xxv. 34.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rt~l AlkalaAma","text_ar":"رتّل الكَلَامَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarotiylN","text_ar":"تَرْتِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He put together and arranged well the component parts of the speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and made it distinct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarotiylu AlquroA=ni","text_ar":"تَرْتِيلُ القُرْا=نِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[explained in what follows]: (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he proceeded in a leisurely manner in the speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"making the utterance distinct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and put together and arranged well its component parts:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rat~alotu AlquroA=na","text_ar":"رَتَّلْتُ القُرْا=نَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. as above,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I read,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recited, the Kur-án in a leisurely manner; without haste:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~arotiylu","text_ar":"التَّرْتِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in reading, or reciting, [and particularly in the reading, or reciting, of the Kur-án,] is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the proceeding in a leisurely manner, and uttering distinctly, without exceeding the proper bounds"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limits:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) [and hence, conventionally,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the chanting"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Kur-án"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a peculiar, distinct, and leisurely, manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY kalaAmihi","text_ar":"فِى كَلَامِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trt~l","text_ar":"ترتّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"فِى الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) signifies [in like manner]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he proceeded in a leisurely manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saying:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) Mujáhid explains"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~arotiyl","text_ar":"التَّرْتِيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the proceeding in a leisurely manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in reading, or reciting], and as being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consecutive in its parts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions;"},{"kind":"text","text":"regarding it as etymologically relating to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vagorN ratilN","text_ar":"ثَغْرٌ رَتِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (T:) accord. to Er-Rághib, it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pronouncing"},{"kind":"text","text":"the word [or words]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with ease and correctness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this is the proper signification: but the conventional meaning, as verified by El-Munáwee, is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the being regardful of the places of utterance of the letters, and mindful of the pauses, and the lowering of the voice, and making it plaintive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in reading, or reciting: (TA:) [accord. to Mtr,] the [proper] meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Altrtyl","text_ar":"الترتيل"},{"kind":"text","text":"in [the reciting, or chanting, of the Kur-án and of] the call to prayer &c. is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pronouncing of the letters in a leisurely manner, and distinctly, and so giving them their proper full sound;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vagorN murat~alN","text_ar":"ثَغْرٌ مُرَتَّلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ratilN","text_ar":"رَتِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ front teeth separate, one from another, and even in the manner of growth, and well set together. ” (Mgh.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarosiylN","text_ar":"تَرْسِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"warat~alonaAhu","text_ar":"وَرَتَّلْنَاهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarotiylFA","text_ar":"تَرْتِيلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxv. 34], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we have sent it down unto thee in a leisurely manner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"we have recited it to thee part after part, in a deliberate and leisurely manner;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in [the course of] twenty years, or three and twenty:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarotiylN","text_ar":"تَرْتِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in its original sense relating to the teeth, and having the signification explained in the beginning of this paragraph. (Bd.)"}],"source_refs":["T","M","K","Msb","S","TA"]}]}}